{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2454af0c-604e-4667-8fe0-9388a8107cd9","content":"## Build Failure Diagnosis\n\n**Solution:** `BuildDiag.sln` — 3 projects, targeting `net8.0`\n\n### Dependency Graph\n```\nCore.csproj          (library, no dependencies)\nServices.csproj      (library, depends on → Core)\nApi.csproj           (exe, depends on → Core, Services)\n```\n\n### Root Cause (1 of 1)\n\n**`Services.csproj` — Missing NuGet package reference for `Newtonsoft.Json`**\n\n3 compiler errors in `Services/UserService.cs`, all `CS0246`:\n\n| Line | Error |\n|------|-------|\n| 2 | `using Newtonsoft.Json;` — namespace not found |\n| 3 | `using Newtonsoft.Json.Linq;` — namespace not found |\n| 22 | `JObject` — type not found |\n\nThe code uses `Newtonsoft.Json` but `Services.csproj` has **no `<PackageReference>` for it**. Current project file only has a `<ProjectReference>` to Core.\n\n### Cascading Failure\n\n**`Api.csproj`** — fails with no errors of its own. It depends on `Services.csproj` via `<ProjectReference>`, so when Services fails to compile, Api cannot resolve its project reference and also fails to build.\n\n### Fix\n\nAdd the missing NuGet package to `Services/Services.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<ItemGroup>\n  <PackageReference Include=\"Newtonsoft.Json\" Version=\"13.*\" />\n</ItemGroup>\n```\n\nNo changes needed for `Core.csproj` or `Api.csproj` — they will build once Services is fixed.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f3d98afc-0b82-492e-8533-bee6c465d3a0","outputTokens":416,"requestId":"5C05:17E76D:1CF213E:20B1A00:6A07C698"},"id":"a595b7c2-7d67-4873-88fc-19b5dc5cf6ce","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:21:46.980Z","parentId":"162308fc-9b48-46af-add9-7073914eb90f"}
